---
name: git-summary
description: Summarize recent git activity in the current repo
allowed-tools: Bash, Read
---

Provide a concise summary of recent git activity:

1. Run `git log --oneline -10` to see recent commits
2. Run `git status` to see working tree state
3. Run `git branch -a` to list branches

Summarize: current branch, clean/dirty state, last few commits, and any notable branches.
Keep the output brief — no more than 10 lines.
